name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.client.failover.connection.retries
description:
Expert only. Indicates the number of retries a failover IPC client
    will make to establish a server connection.

name: dfs.namenode.block.deletion.increment
description:
The number of block deletion increment.
      This setting will control the block increment deletion rate to
      ensure that other waiters on the lock can get in.

name: hadoop.registry.zk.retry.times
description: Zookeeper connection retry count before failing

name: dfs.namenode.fs-limits.max-xattrs-per-inode
description: Maximum number of extended attributes per inode.

name: dfs.client.failover.connection.retries.on.timeouts
description:
Expert only. The number of retry attempts a failover IPC client
    will make on socket timeout when establishing a server connection.

name: fs.permissions.umask-mode
description:
The umask used when creating files and directories.
    Can be in octal or in symbolic. Examples are:
    "022" (octal for u=rwx,g=r-x,o=r-x in symbolic),
    or "u=rwx,g=rwx,o=" (symbolic for 007 in octal).
